Additionally, the growing focus on sustainability and energy efficiency is influencing the development of semiconductor IP solutions. With environmental concerns becoming more prominent, there is a shift towards designing power-efficient and eco-friendly semiconductor components that minimize energy consumption and reduce carbon footprint. Market players are investing in R&D efforts to create energy-optimized IP cores, power management solutions, and green computing technologies that align with global sustainability goals and regulations.

